{
    "title": "Have You Ever?",
    "level": "A2",
    "pattern": {
        "title": "Spoken perfect: oon käyny, ootsä ollu",
        "summary": "To say what you have done, use 'olla' + a participle: mä oon käyny = I've been / visited. In spoken Finnish the participle drops its final -t: käynyt → käyny, ollut → ollu, syönyt → syöny. The negative is 'en oo' + the same form: en oo käyny.",
        "examples": [
            "Mä oon käyny Tallinnas. = I've been to Tallinn.",
            "Ootsä jo syöny? = Have you eaten yet?",
            "En oo ikinä kokeillu. = I've never tried it."
        ]
    },
    "sentences": [
